                    LAB EXERCISES
EX.NO:05
                EXTERNAL STYLE SHEETS
AIM:
   To design a webpage of your college with attractive background color, text-color, font-face, an image by using external CSS formatting.
PROCEDURE:
1.	Start the notepad and write HTML document with <html> tag.
2.	Create a head section using <head> tag and set a title using the <title> tag.
3.	Start the body section using <body> tag.
4.	Create style.css for styling.
5.  Set background-color, color, and font-family.
6.  Style images with width, border, or margin.
7.  Add a heading for the college name.
8.  Add a short description using <p> or <div>.
9.  Insert a college image with <img>.
10. Save both files in the same folder and open HTML in a browser.
PROGRAM:
EX-NO-05.html:
  <!DOCTYPE html>
  <html lang="en">
  <head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <title>College Webpage</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="EX-NO-05.css">
  </head>
  <body>
  <header>
  <h1>Welcome to XXX Polytechnic College</h1>
  </header>
  <main>
  <section id="about">
  <h2>About Us</h2>
  <p>
  XXX Polytechnic College is a prestigious institution offering a variety of courses and programs. 
  Our vision is to impart quality education, skills, and attributes based on continuously changing global standards and local industrial requirements.
  </p>
  <img src="college.jpg" alt="College">
  </section>
  </main>
  <footer>
  <p>&copy; 2024 XXX Polytechnic College. All rights reserved.</p>
  </footer>
  </body>
  </html>
EX-NO-05.css:
  body {
  font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
  text-align: center;
  background-color: #f9f9f9;
  margin: 20px;
  }
  table {
  width: 80%;
  margin: 0 auto;
  border-collapse: collapse;
  background-color: #fff;
  border: 2px solid #004080;
  }
  th, td {
  padding: 10px;
  text-align: center;
  border: 1.5px solid #004080;
  }
  th {
  background-color: #004080;
  color: white;
  }
  tr:nth-child(even) {
  background-color: #f2f2f2;
  }
RESULT:
    Thus the above HTML Code is executed and the output is obtained.
